rComments: Amazing class with the best teacher I have had in a long while. With amazing quotes and a very informative class.
Prof. Thompson is a good teacher, super helpful, and unintentionally hilarious!

This guy cracks me up.  He can be terribly boring, but every once in a while a complete gem will come out of his mouth.  He's a very nice guy, but his grading policy is just plain stupid.  He grades things in a continuum, so even if your work is fine, if 20 people do better than you, you will not get an A.
Unclear grading scale and confusing tests. Not the class for you if astronomy is not your major.
A lot of materials to study, but the tests are not too bad. The professor is such a kind and nice guy. Since there are so much to study, I think it's important to do the readings for every class..
This guy has to be an alien.  "Now just for fun..."  He is very straightforward in how the class is presented.  Very dry sense of humor.  Class isn't the easiest, but Thompson tries to help.
not the cutest old man that ive ever seen... hiw "whatevers" did make me laugh however.
attractive man. extremely intelligent and interesting. his "whatevers" always make me laugh. fair grader, tests not too hard
I must agree, one cute old man. Very nice (especially to girls--his face turns red every time he talks to a girl face 2 face). ha.  But very hard course.
He IS a cute old man, but SO BORING!  I fell asleep about every day.  He's really concerned about cheating, too...  He's a hard grader, and has a strange grading system.  Remember:  VERY BORING
Likes to say whatever alot, comments on  cute equations  and is funny
